  "response": "Green Cheek Conures and Sun Conures have several key differences:\n\n1. Size:\n- Green Cheek Conures are smaller (around 10 inches long)\n- Sun Conures are larger (around 12 inches long)\n\n2. Coloration:\n- Green Cheek: Primarily green with gray/black head and red tail feathers\n- Sun Conures: Bright yellow, orange, and red with green wing edges\n\n3. Personality:\n- Green Cheek: Generally quieter, more calm, and less demanding\n- Sun Conures: More vocal, energetic, and can be louder\n\n4. Noise Level:\n- Green Cheek: Relatively quiet\n- Sun Conures: Very loud and prone to screeching\n\n5. Temperament:\n- Green Cheek: Usually gentler and more cuddly\n- Sun Conures: More active and can be more nippy\n\n6. Price:\n- Green Cheek: Typically less expensive\n- Sun Conures: Generally more costly\n\n7. Lifespan:\n- Both have similar lifespans of 20-30 years with proper care\n\n8. Intelligence:\n- Both are considered intelligent and trainable, with slight variations in learning styles\n\nThese differences can help potential owners choose the right conure for their lifestyle.",
